Try it out locally

Build:

dotnet build


Initialize repo:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- init

Generate keys:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- keygen

Add:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- add

Make a commit:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- commit "Initial commit"


View log:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- log

Versions:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- checkout

Restore:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- checkout <Hash>

Remote:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI --remote add origin [http://127.0.0.1:9000](http://127.0.0.1:9000) my-project my-bucket minioadmin minioadmin123

List:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI --remote list

Push:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI --push origin

Pull:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI --pull origin

Verify a commit:
dotnet run --project CodeFlow.CLI -- verify <commit-hash>


Roadmap of What We’re Building

✅ CLI Base (done) – init, add, commit, checkout, log, verify.

🚀 Large File Support – detect & offload to remote backend.

🌐 Remote Repos – push/pull commits + objects between peers or cloud.

🔒 Decentralization Layer – peer-to-peer sync (no single point of failure).

🎯 Integration Layer – optional GitHub/Git compatibility for collab.